constructor.details: The owner of the contract is set to be the sender of the deployment transaction

deposit().details: Emits YoyoNft__DepositCompleted event with amount and timestampReverts with YoyoNft__ValueCantBeZero if msg.value is zero

returns._0: uint256 The number of NFTs owned by the account
address The immutable auction contract address
uint256 The basic mint price in wei

getIfTokenIdIsMintable(uint256).details: Verifies both whether it has already been minted and whether the ID is within the maximum supply

params._tokenId: The unique ID of the token to check

returns._0: bool True if the token is mintable, false otherwise

params.tokenId: The unique ID of the token

returns._0: address The address of the token owner
uint256 The current token counter value

mintNft(address,uint256).details: Implementation of the safeMint function from ERC721 standardCreates the event with all the information for the frontend like tokenURI and tokenIdUpdates tokenCounter to avoid max supply exceedEmits YoyoNft__NftMinted event with recipient, tokenId, tokenURI and timestampReverts with YoyoNft__NftMaxSupplyReached if max supply is reachedReverts with YoyoNft__NftAlreadyMinted if token is already mintedReverts with YoyoNft__TokenIdDoesNotExist if tokenId >= MAX_NFT_SUPPLYReverts with YoyoNft__NotEnoughEtherSent if msg.value < basicMintPriceReverts with YoyoNft__InvalidAddress if recipient is address(0)

params._to: The recipient to whom the NFT will be sent immediately after it is minted
params._tokenId: The unique ID of the token to be minted

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBasicMintPrice(uint256).details: This is because the logic of the auction contract must prevent the winner'sauction price from being in any way lower than the mint price, which wouldresult in the minting process failingEmits YoyoNft__MintPriceUpdated eventReverts with YoyoNft__ValueCantBeZero if new price is zero

params._newBasicPrice: The new minting price in wei

tokenURI(uint256).details: Reverts with YoyoNft__TokenIdDoesNotExist if tokenId >= MAX_NFT_SUPPLYReverts with YoyoNft__NftNotMinted if token has not been minted yet

params._tokenId: The unique ID of the token

returns._0: string The complete unique URI related to the specific token

transferNft(address,uint256).details: Implementation of the safeTransfer function from ERC721 standardReverts with YoyoNft__InvalidAddress if recipient is address(0)Reverts with YoyoNft__NotNftOwner if caller is not the owner of the token

params._to: The recipient to whom the NFT will be sent
params._tokenId: The unique ID of the token to send

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw().details: Transfers entire contract balance to the ownerEmits YoyoNft__WithdrawCompleted event on successReverts with YoyoNft__ContractBalanceIsZero if balance is zeroReverts with YoyoNft__WithdrawFailed if transfer fails

MAX_NFT_SUPPLY().notice: Maximum number of NFTs that can be minted in this collection

constructor.notice: The ERC721 token is inizialized with the name "Yoyo Collection" and with the symbol "YOYO"

deposit().notice: Allows only the owner of the contract to deposit funds

getAccountBalance(address).notice: Returns the number of NFTs owned by a specific account

getAuctionContract().notice: Returns the address of the auction contract

getBaseURI().notice: Returns the base URI for token metadata

getBasicMintPrice().notice: Returns the current basic mint price for NFTs

getIfTokenIdIsMintable(uint256).notice: Checks whether a specific token ID can be minted or not

getOwnerFromTokenId(uint256).notice: Returns the owner of a specific token ID

getTotalMinted().notice: Returns the total number of NFTs minted so far

mintNft(address,uint256).notice: Allows the auction contract to mint a new NFT to send to the auction winner

setBasicMintPrice(uint256).notice: Allows the auction contract to set the base minting price

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Returns the complete URI of a specific token from its ID

transferNft(address,uint256).notice: Allows NFT owner to transfer their NFT to another user

withdraw().notice: Allows only the owner of the contract to withdraw funds from contract
